quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
36,71,"Do they not see Our handiwork: {1} We created for them cattle which they own?",footnotes:1:The word “hands” has been used metaphorically for Allah. This does not mean that
36,72,"We have subjected the cattle to them so that some of them they ride and eat the flesh of others."
36,73,"They derive a variety of benefits and drinks from them. Will they, then, not give thanks? {1}",footnotes:1:It is ingratitude to regard a blessing as a gift of someone other than the donor
36,74,"They set up deities apart from Allah, hoping that they will receive help from them."
36,75,"Those deities can render them no help. Yet these devotees act as though they were an army in waiting for them. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
36,76,"Let not their words grieve you. Surely We know all things about them, what they conceal and what they reveal. {1}",footnotes:1:The address is to the Prophet (peace be upon him). Here the allusion is to the campaign of vilification which the chiefs of the disbelievers of Makkah were carrying on against him. They knew in their hearts and acknowledged in their private assemblies that the charges they brought against him were absolutely baseless. In order to create suspicions against him in the minds of the people
36,77,"Does {1} man not see that We created him of a sperm drop, and lo! he is flagrantly contentious? {2}",footnotes:1:That is
36,78,"He strikes for Us {1} a similitude and forgot his own creation. {2} He says: “Who will quicken the bones when they have decayed?”",footnotes:1:That is
36,79,"Say: “He Who first brought them into being will quicken them; He knows well about every kind of creation;"
36,80,"He Who created from a green tree a fire for you, a fire to light your stoves with.” {1}",footnotes:1:It either means that He has placed the inflammable matter in the green trees due to which people kindle fire from the pieces of wood. Or
36,81,"Has He Who created the heavens and the earth no power to create the likes of them? Yes, indeed, He is the Superb Creator."
36,82,"Whenever He wills a thing, He just commands it “Be” and it is."
36,83,"Holy is He Who has full control over everything, and to Him you shall all be recalled."
